02:32:08.080 --> 02:32:15.080
I said, okay, she said, well, why don't you come on and throw the first piece?

02:32:15.080 --> 02:32:18.080
I said, I'm not having nothing to do with the Red Sox.

02:32:20.080 --> 02:32:22.080
She said, well, the Red Sox has changed.

02:32:22.080 --> 02:32:23.080
This is different.

02:32:23.080 --> 02:32:33.080
I said, well, you show me that you have a program to facilitate the change.

02:32:34.080 --> 02:32:36.080
Maybe we'll talk.

02:32:36.080 --> 02:32:38.080
That doesn't mean I'm comfortable with it.

02:32:38.080 --> 02:32:41.080
I said, you're not going to keep the same policy.

02:32:41.080 --> 02:32:44.080
It give Bill Russell come through at the first pitch.

02:32:44.080 --> 02:32:47.080
And, say, see, we've changed.

02:32:47.080 --> 02:32:50.080
That's not just not going to happen.

02:32:50.080 --> 02:32:58.080
So, fast forward, I have a charity that I've been working with for almost 20 years.

02:32:58.080 --> 02:33:00.080
It's called Mentoring.

02:33:00.080 --> 02:33:03.080
It's called Mentoring.

02:33:03.080 --> 02:33:09.080
And we have so far a very successful program.

02:33:09.080 --> 02:33:15.080
We started out with a name one to one, one mentor, one mentor.

02:33:15.080 --> 02:33:26.080
Last year, 2012, we passed eight million volunteers to our country.

02:33:26.080 --> 02:33:29.080
Four million, I'm sorry.

02:33:29.080 --> 02:33:35.080
Four million volunteers throughout the country that are one to one mentoring.

02:33:35.080 --> 02:33:44.080
But it's not just black kids.

02:33:44.080 --> 02:33:47.080
It's kids.

02:33:47.080 --> 02:33:55.080
In the Boston chapter, we've got a lot of Hispanic kids.

02:33:55.080 --> 02:33:58.080
Loss of Hispanic kids.

02:33:58.080 --> 02:34:01.080
Loss of black kids.

02:34:01.080 --> 02:34:03.080
A lot of white kids.

02:34:03.080 --> 02:34:07.080
The only requirement is you be a kid.

02:34:07.080 --> 02:34:14.080
And someone who spent some time helping you get started.

02:34:14.080 --> 02:34:24.080
And we have found that this adult's that volunteered to be mentors end up profiting more than the kids.

02:34:24.080 --> 02:34:31.080
Because you find out on a very personal basis how you can be helpful.

02:34:31.080 --> 02:34:36.080
So, you asked the Red Sox to become active?

02:34:36.080 --> 02:34:42.080
Well, I asked Red Sox. They had three or four owners.

02:34:42.080 --> 02:34:49.080
I said, I want one of those owners to go on the board of my charity.

02:34:50.080 --> 02:34:55.080
Not to say we support it. Go on the board.

02:34:55.080 --> 02:34:58.080
They said, well, don't you want to play? I said, no, I don't want to play.

02:34:58.080 --> 02:35:01.080
There's nothing I don't restrict to players or not.

02:35:01.080 --> 02:35:08.080
But the owners can make policy decisions.

02:35:08.080 --> 02:35:14.080
And the owners are not likely to get trained in the way.

02:35:14.080 --> 02:35:18.080
So, they're players or the Red Sox.

02:35:18.080 --> 02:35:33.080
As far as I'm talking, nice, nice, much of young guys who are prone to be active in the community.

02:35:33.080 --> 02:35:38.080
And so, I said, but it's not insulting. It's not important.

02:35:38.080 --> 02:35:45.080
I want somebody from Red Sox that can make decisions and policy.

02:35:45.080 --> 02:35:53.080
So, we got one of the owners to go on the board.

02:35:53.080 --> 02:35:56.080
And he's done an absolutely marvelous job.

02:35:56.080 --> 02:36:03.080
In fact, most of the people are doing them think that mentoring is a Red Sox program.

02:36:03.080 --> 02:36:06.080
I can live with that.

02:36:06.080 --> 02:36:10.080
Because that's the biggest voice in doing it. It's a Red Sox.

02:36:10.080 --> 02:36:15.080
And they were all out.

02:36:15.080 --> 02:36:20.080
That's your fault.

02:36:20.080 --> 02:36:23.080
We're going.

02:36:23.080 --> 02:36:29.080
So, the Red Sox stepped up to meet your conditions and support the mentoring.

02:36:29.080 --> 02:36:36.080
Yes. What they did was they got twice a year at Fenway Park.

02:36:36.080 --> 02:36:39.080
They have stepped up to play for mentoring.

02:36:39.080 --> 02:36:45.080
And on the green monster, they have a better.

02:36:45.080 --> 02:36:49.080
They listed number of people they brought into the mentoring program.

02:36:49.080 --> 02:36:56.080
And for every Red Sox game, there are four seats set aside for two mentors and two mentees

02:36:56.080 --> 02:36:59.080
that have been together for three years or more.

02:36:59.080 --> 02:37:02.080
They're the guests in the Red Sox.

02:37:02.080 --> 02:37:05.080
And they've encouraged their sponsors.

02:37:05.080 --> 02:37:11.080
And they're all...

02:37:11.080 --> 02:37:19.080
Well, anyway, they encourage people to do business with them to start mentoring programs and their companies.

02:37:19.080 --> 02:37:22.080
So, they've been really super.

02:37:22.080 --> 02:37:27.080
So, when did somebody from the Red Sox call you up and say,

02:37:27.080 --> 02:37:30.080
we think we've met your conditions.

02:37:30.080 --> 02:37:33.080
We've tried to make a change. Are you ready to throw out the first ball?

02:37:33.080 --> 02:37:36.080
I did.

02:37:36.080 --> 02:37:41.080
I didn't get it over the plate though.

02:37:41.080 --> 02:37:45.080
Wow. How long ago was that that you threw out the first pitch?

02:37:45.080 --> 02:37:48.080
Well, it must have been... maybe six years ago.

02:37:48.080 --> 02:37:50.080
So, after they won the World Series?

02:37:50.080 --> 02:37:53.080
Yes.

02:37:53.080 --> 02:37:58.080
Because my late wife and I were back there a couple times.

02:37:58.080 --> 02:38:03.080
And Red Sox did some very nice.

02:38:03.080 --> 02:38:09.080
They started scholarship for one of the city kids in Boston.

02:38:09.080 --> 02:38:14.080
And named it a male or not, Russell scholarship.

02:38:14.080 --> 02:38:16.080
And...

02:38:16.080 --> 02:38:18.080
And named it from Aaron.

02:38:18.080 --> 02:38:20.080
Yes.

02:38:20.080 --> 02:38:25.080
And I didn't really please me a lot because that was my good friend.

02:38:25.080 --> 02:38:30.080
And so, then how long after that was it to the city of Boston?

02:38:30.080 --> 02:38:34.080
Was it the mayor who approached you about the statue?

02:38:34.080 --> 02:38:38.080
Yeah, well, after I got to the Medal of Freedom,

02:38:38.080 --> 02:38:43.080
and Obama says, somebody there will be a statue of Boston from Bill Russell.

02:38:43.080 --> 02:38:50.080
And I told him I never put a giving for that.

02:38:50.080 --> 02:38:52.080
Because when Tom...

02:38:52.080 --> 02:38:54.080
Oh, man, they don't want to tell me about the statue.

02:38:54.080 --> 02:39:04.080
I said, you know, it sounds a me a lot like a tombstone.

02:39:04.080 --> 02:39:06.080
And he says, why don't you say that?

02:39:06.080 --> 02:39:09.080
I said, well, you know,

02:39:09.080 --> 02:39:16.080
if you really, truly believe in God,

02:39:16.080 --> 02:39:21.080
he does not need a marker to find you.

02:39:21.080 --> 02:39:25.080
So I said, I would be willing to be buried in an unmarked grave.

02:39:25.080 --> 02:39:28.080
But, of course, if you really believe in God,

02:39:28.080 --> 02:39:30.080
he doesn't need a marker to find you.

02:39:30.080 --> 02:39:33.080
He was exactly where you are.

02:39:33.080 --> 02:39:37.080
And so, what Tom says, well, I said, besides that,

02:39:37.080 --> 02:39:40.080
I don't need anything like that.

02:39:40.080 --> 02:39:46.080
He says, well, it's not so much for you, it is for the city.

02:39:46.080 --> 02:40:03.080
You've made our tremendous amount of difference in community and racial relations.

02:40:04.080 --> 02:40:12.080
Of course, my way of thinking,

02:40:12.080 --> 02:40:18.080
I've not got past the place where we were beyond race.

02:40:18.080 --> 02:40:24.080
Even I had dead dome.

02:40:24.080 --> 02:40:30.080
But, that can be, if you wanted to be,

02:40:30.080 --> 02:40:33.080
a healthy part of community relations,

02:40:33.080 --> 02:40:37.080
that's the answer difference.

02:40:37.080 --> 02:40:44.080
When they found out that, when I made decisions,

02:40:44.080 --> 02:40:49.080
it was based on competence, not on race.

02:40:49.080 --> 02:40:52.080
And that's all they didn't want to ask them anybody,

02:40:52.080 --> 02:40:58.080
is that, oh, if you're going to make a decision

02:40:58.080 --> 02:41:04.080
and race becomes a part of your decision-making process,

02:41:04.080 --> 02:41:09.080
which you have to really go to is competence.

02:41:09.080 --> 02:41:14.080
And, like I always say, long ago,

02:41:14.080 --> 02:41:18.080
so that's me, what would I think about a gay person planning MBA?

02:41:18.080 --> 02:41:22.080
This was years and years and years ago.

02:41:22.080 --> 02:41:26.080
And I said, have one question.

02:41:26.080 --> 02:41:32.080
What would you like to do if you could get a job?

02:41:32.080 --> 02:41:35.080
I don't know.

02:41:35.080 --> 02:41:38.080
I don't know.

02:41:38.080 --> 02:41:41.080
I don't know.

02:41:41.080 --> 02:41:44.080
I don't know.

02:41:44.080 --> 02:41:48.080
I don't know.

02:41:48.080 --> 02:41:51.080
I don't know.

02:41:51.080 --> 02:41:55.080
I don't know.

02:41:55.080 --> 02:42:03.080
If we do this, we're going to have you make all the key decisions.

02:42:03.080 --> 02:42:07.080
And, first, I looked at five different sites in Boston,

02:42:07.080 --> 02:42:13.080
with the city manager, to see where we're going to put it.

02:42:13.080 --> 02:42:18.080
And we ended up at City Hall Plaza,

02:42:18.080 --> 02:42:23.080
which is adjacent to the Freedom Trail

02:42:23.080 --> 02:42:26.080
and near the old state house.

02:42:26.080 --> 02:42:35.080
And we're going to put a little bit of an alley,

02:42:35.080 --> 02:42:38.080
but it's going to be like the Valley of Champions.

02:42:38.080 --> 02:42:41.080
And so for all the teams at the White Championship,

02:42:41.080 --> 02:42:43.080
both have a star.

02:42:43.080 --> 02:42:46.080
Lead up to the statue.

02:42:46.080 --> 02:42:51.080
And it will have some of my pet phrases like,

02:42:51.080 --> 02:42:55.080
they're those such things as other people's kids.

02:42:55.080 --> 02:42:59.080
They're all next generation Americans.

02:42:59.080 --> 02:43:03.080
And a few things like that.

02:43:03.080 --> 02:43:05.080
On the statue.

02:43:05.080 --> 02:43:08.080
Knowing the little plaques all around.

02:43:08.080 --> 02:43:16.080
So, but Tom did not have me convinced yet.

02:43:16.080 --> 02:43:23.080
And so, he says, okay, we're going to set up a legacy foundation

02:43:23.080 --> 02:43:28.080
to support mentoring.

02:43:28.080 --> 02:43:32.080
And so every year we'll have fun races around the statue

02:43:32.080 --> 02:43:36.080
to raise money for mentoring.

02:43:36.080 --> 02:43:44.080
And that's a good way to get real personal community involvement

02:43:44.080 --> 02:43:48.080
in the educational system.

02:43:48.080 --> 02:43:52.080
And when you get that,

02:43:52.080 --> 02:43:56.080
you see like I saw a thing on TV the other day

02:43:56.080 --> 02:44:00.080
that in terms of literacy and all that kind of stuff,

02:44:00.080 --> 02:44:04.080
America's in the second 10.

02:44:04.080 --> 02:44:10.080
Well, how are you going to maintain a viable

02:44:10.080 --> 02:44:12.080
part of the future?

02:44:12.080 --> 02:44:17.080
If you don't educate the next generation.

02:44:17.080 --> 02:44:24.080
And the only way you can beat that is start a war.

02:44:24.080 --> 02:44:26.080
Right.

02:44:26.080 --> 02:44:35.080
And so, I don't think wars are helpful.

02:44:35.080 --> 02:44:38.080
You mentioned getting the medal of freedom from President Obama.

02:44:38.080 --> 02:44:40.080
What was that experience like?

02:44:40.080 --> 02:44:43.080
I understand that he was a great athlete.

02:44:43.080 --> 02:44:46.080
I think he's an extraordinary nice man, first of all,

02:44:46.080 --> 02:44:50.080
and a good person.

02:44:50.080 --> 02:44:52.080
But they asked me is that the highest I've ever got.

02:44:52.080 --> 02:44:56.080
And I said just second.

02:44:56.080 --> 02:45:00.080
And I said second, yeah.

02:45:00.080 --> 02:45:03.080
Second?

02:45:03.080 --> 02:45:04.080
Yeah.

02:45:04.080 --> 02:45:08.080
Well, if that's second, what was the highest honor?

02:45:08.080 --> 02:45:12.080
Well, when he was 75, my father said to me one day,

02:45:12.080 --> 02:45:14.080
you know, I'm very proud of you.

02:45:14.080 --> 02:45:18.080
That's my son.

02:45:18.080 --> 02:45:23.080
I'm also proud that I'm your father.

02:45:23.080 --> 02:45:28.080
And this is my hero.

02:45:28.080 --> 02:45:31.080
And you can't talk to that.

02:45:31.080 --> 02:45:35.080
You're not coming from the hero.

02:45:35.080 --> 02:45:37.080
But it was a good second, right?

02:45:37.080 --> 02:45:40.080
Oh, yeah, it was a good strong second.

02:45:40.080 --> 02:45:44.080
What did he say about you're helping him become President?

02:45:44.080 --> 02:45:50.080
He just said that it was a guy like me that made it possible

02:45:50.080 --> 02:45:57.080
for him to be President.

02:45:57.080 --> 02:46:02.080
I don't see that, but thanks anyway.

02:46:02.080 --> 02:46:08.080
I really like him on a personal basis.

02:46:08.080 --> 02:46:16.080
The first time I met him, we were dedicating the start of the work

02:46:16.080 --> 02:46:21.080
on the monitor king, the monitor, and Washington.

02:46:21.080 --> 02:46:24.080
And so he was with me.

02:46:24.080 --> 02:46:31.080
I know you care and Russell's dead.

02:46:31.080 --> 02:46:38.080
And you were the same thing Bill Clinton said to the first time I met him.

02:46:38.080 --> 02:46:45.080
You know, and so this feels fun to be a parent and have so much to that.

02:46:45.080 --> 02:46:51.080
I said, what about Chuck Limbaugh?

02:46:51.080 --> 02:46:56.080
You also mentioned speaking of mentors and role models

02:46:56.080 --> 02:47:01.080
that you were the only basketball pole bearer for Jackie Robinson.

02:47:01.080 --> 02:47:03.080
Is that right? How did that come about?

02:47:03.080 --> 02:47:04.080
All in none teammate.

02:47:04.080 --> 02:47:06.080
The only non-brooklandager teammate.

02:47:06.080 --> 02:47:10.080
Right.

02:47:10.080 --> 02:47:16.080
Well, when Jackie started with the Dodgers, I was 13.

02:47:16.080 --> 02:47:25.080
And he was the essence of an athletic hero.

02:47:25.080 --> 02:47:32.080
He was the main player of the football team.

02:47:32.080 --> 02:47:39.080
He was the main player of the football team.

02:47:39.080 --> 02:47:47.080
At the time of a children, there was nobody like that.

02:47:47.080 --> 02:47:54.080
There were many guys that had no money, but they were not stand-up guys.

02:47:54.080 --> 02:47:59.080
And so when Jackie died, Rachel Robinson called me and said,

02:47:59.080 --> 02:48:04.080
I want you to be a pole bearer at Jackie's Field Room.

02:48:04.080 --> 02:48:08.080
Well, that's right up there with a close number three.

02:48:08.080 --> 02:48:10.080
Okay.

02:48:10.080 --> 02:48:17.080
And so I said, of course, just tell me when it were.

02:48:17.080 --> 02:48:22.080
I'm not a lot of kids from the projects in West Oakland.

02:48:22.080 --> 02:48:27.080
I get to be a pole bearer for Jackie Robinson.

02:48:27.080 --> 02:48:33.080
And so I said, why me?

02:48:33.080 --> 02:48:39.080
She said, you were Jackie's favorite athlete.

02:48:39.080 --> 02:48:42.080
Well, as far as fans and all that kind of stuff,

02:48:42.080 --> 02:48:46.080
nobody else comes close to that.

02:48:46.080 --> 02:48:53.080
You know, Jackie was our guy as a kid.

02:48:53.080 --> 02:48:58.080
I was saying that he turned around and respected me.

02:48:58.080 --> 02:49:02.080
And I took the attitude because of that.

02:49:02.080 --> 02:49:11.080
What I thought about it, I said, Jackie took us for a four day to point B.

02:49:11.080 --> 02:49:16.080
First black guy in the Asian League sports baseball.

02:49:16.080 --> 02:49:20.080
Well, what I got with the Celtics,

02:49:20.080 --> 02:49:27.080
I did not want to revisit that point A to point B.

02:49:27.080 --> 02:49:31.080
I want to go point B to point C.

02:49:31.080 --> 02:49:40.080
That's why I was kind of happy with the point that I coach.

02:49:40.080 --> 02:49:50.080
And look at how important it is that you're the first black coach.

02:49:50.080 --> 02:49:52.080
I say it's not important.

02:49:52.080 --> 02:49:57.080
First of all, I'm the best person for this particular job.

02:49:57.080 --> 02:50:00.080
And I know that.

02:50:00.080 --> 02:50:06.080
And second, it'll be important.

02:50:06.080 --> 02:50:12.080
The coaches are hired and fired with no reference to race.

02:50:12.080 --> 02:50:17.080
Then it's important.

02:50:17.080 --> 02:50:25.080
So like now coaches are and managers are fired wholesale.

02:50:25.080 --> 02:50:27.080
Okay.

02:50:27.080 --> 02:50:33.080
And nowadays, never is there reference to race.

02:50:33.080 --> 02:50:40.080
We should speak just a little bit here toward the end because we mentioned Jackie as a role model.

02:50:40.080 --> 02:50:45.080
And about your relationship with some, we've talked about your teammates,

02:50:45.080 --> 02:50:52.080
but you also had some pretty celebrated rivals that you said your reaction with your relations with your adversaries

02:50:52.080 --> 02:50:56.080
were special because they made you play better.

02:50:56.080 --> 02:50:58.080
Well, that was it.

02:50:58.080 --> 02:51:01.080
And Wilton and Elgin Baylor.

02:51:01.080 --> 02:51:08.080
Not only that, but at that time with the NBA,

02:51:08.080 --> 02:51:19.080
I was really seriously wished that every player in NBA could find a position where he could play his best.

02:51:19.080 --> 02:51:26.080
Because then the people with the NBA games would see the best players in the world playing their best.

02:51:26.080 --> 02:51:33.080
I kicked the ass at their best.

02:51:33.080 --> 02:51:47.080
But that in a way, didn't that indirectly lead to your part of your feud?

02:51:47.080 --> 02:51:51.080
I guess it's not quite the right word with Wilton because he didn't play in your last game

02:51:51.080 --> 02:51:54.080
and you wanted him to make you earn it that last championship.

02:51:54.080 --> 02:51:58.080
Well, no, you know, I talked to Wilton about that.

02:51:58.080 --> 02:52:04.080
And I looked him to eye and I said, Wilton, I apologize for the stuff I said.

02:52:04.080 --> 02:52:07.080
That was just humorous.

02:52:07.080 --> 02:52:10.080
You know, it was my last game, not new it.

02:52:10.080 --> 02:52:19.080
And nothing more than anything to make it less pleasant to me.

02:52:20.080 --> 02:52:33.080
And I said things about him that I should not have said was I was speaking to a college group in Iowa, I think.

02:52:33.080 --> 02:52:37.080
And there was a reporter in there mixed in with the kids.

02:52:37.080 --> 02:52:40.080
I had a noise reporter.

02:52:40.080 --> 02:52:42.080
And so we do this question actually.

02:52:42.080 --> 02:52:48.080
He said, well, you never want that last championship in Wilton got hurt.

02:52:48.080 --> 02:52:51.080
Well, it annoyed me.

02:52:51.080 --> 02:52:56.080
Of course, in Wilton after game, we were 17 points ahead.

02:52:56.080 --> 02:53:02.080
You know, and I went off on the Wilton and he had nothing to do with it.

02:53:02.080 --> 02:53:08.080
And so I looked him and I and apologized to him and said it was just humorous.

02:53:08.080 --> 02:53:12.080
I was not on that.

02:53:12.080 --> 02:53:13.080
I was wrong.

02:53:13.080 --> 02:53:16.080
But you did want him to be in the game because...

02:53:17.080 --> 02:53:18.080
Yeah, because...

02:53:18.080 --> 02:53:19.080
Something out of the competition.

02:53:19.080 --> 02:53:22.080
Well, no, also, it was easy game.

02:53:22.080 --> 02:53:25.080
We said deep voice ahead.

02:53:25.080 --> 02:53:32.080
I don't want to change that.

02:53:32.080 --> 02:53:37.080
You said once in one of your books here about Dr. King, I don't want...

02:53:37.080 --> 02:53:42.080
I had the same reservation about Dr. King that I had about the Vietnam War,

02:53:43.080 --> 02:53:46.080
which is that the white people in Boston liked him.

02:53:46.080 --> 02:53:49.080
So I knew something must be wrong.

02:53:49.080 --> 02:53:52.080
I guess that's a light moment.

02:53:52.080 --> 02:53:57.080
Because there was a time when they were kind of superficial about race relations.

02:53:57.080 --> 02:54:06.080
